name: James
description:
The Holland Codes are a system of personality typology developed by psychologist John. L. Holland with the idea that people’s personalities are analogous to the types of occupations they prefer. The system measures people on six separate scales of which the three highest scores in order represent individuals type.

The original Holland Code test, called the Self-Directed Search, used forced choice preferences. This test use the public domain RIASEC markers from the Interest Item Pool.

name: Rory
description:
The following six stories describe six different Helpers trying to help six different people. The six different people have similar serious problems. It is now time to decide whether to support each Helper’s plan to improve the person’s situation. The six Helpers equally care for the people. They highly recommend and provide the same basic plans to help the person, but carry them out in different ways. In the following six paragraphs, the Helpers' accurate accounts of their usual interaction with each person are given. Please rate each Helper’s method by answering the questions that follow. A rating of 1 means you strongly disagree with the method of the helper. A rating of 6 means you strongly agree with the method of the Helper.

Each paragraph consists of many similar simple sentences. However, they are organized in different ways. Pay attention to how good each Helper's method is. You can read all the stories before you rate any of them, but in the end please be sure to rate every question. Thank you!

name: Rory
name1: Assessment of Development with Autism Spectrum Disorder using Autism Developmental Task Sequence
description: The purpose of this study is to create an instrument for measuring the development of autistic children and adults. The study assesses their development according to the stages and domains of the Model of Hierarchical Complexity (MHC). The creation of such an instrument is vital towards the assessment for the purpose of designing interventions and giving diagnostics. The expectation is that, with the instrument, and diagnostic, progress of the autistic children and adults can be tracked accordingly place them in the stages of MHC. This placement will be further helpful in designing behavioral and education materials and procedures and to further research and innovation in the field.
